---
import LegalLayout from "~/layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
import { getLocalizedPath } from "~/i18n/utils";

const privacy = getLocalizedPath("/privacy", "en");

const title = "AwesomeBot Subprocessor List";
const description =
  "The entities AwesomeWorks entrusts with data processing to run AwesomeBot — role, data categories and processing location.";
---

<LegalLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  eyebrow="Data processing"
  heading="Subprocessor List"
  lastUpdated="Effective 10 July 2026"
  slugs={{ pl: "/podprocesorzy", en: "/subprocessors" }}
>
  <p class="legal-lead">
    Below are the entities (subprocessors) that AwesomeWorks entrusts with processing personal data
    to provide the AwesomeBot service. This list forms part of the data processing agreement (DPA)
    concluded with Clients.
  </p>
  <p>
    We have an agreement with each entity ensuring an adequate level of data protection and — for
    transfers outside the European Economic Area — Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC). Processing is
    described in the <a href={privacy}>Privacy Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">1.</span>Operational subprocessors</h2>
  <div class="legal-table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Subprocessor</th>
          <th>Role and purpose</th>
          <th>Data categories</th>
          <th>Location</th>
          <th>Transfer basis</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>OpenAI</strong><br />OpenAI, L.L.C. / OpenAI Ireland Ltd.</td>
          <td>Language models (classification, reply drafting), speech transcription (Whisper), vector embeddings.</td>
          <td>Message content, transcripts of calls and voicemail, contact details within content.</td>
          <td>USA (outside EEA)</td>
          <td>DPA + SCC</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>ElevenLabs</strong><br />ElevenLabs Inc.</td>
          <td>Speech synthesis (TTS) and the voice-agent platform; storage of call recordings.</td>
          <td>Voice call recordings and content, transcripts, conversation identifier.</td>
          <td>Data residency</td>
          <td>DPA</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Telnyx</strong><br />Telnyx LLC</td>
          <td>Telephony: numbers, routing of inbound calls and SMS.</td>
          <td>Phone numbers, call metadata.</td>
          <td><strong>Germany (EU)</strong></td>
          <td>DPA</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Twilio</strong><br />Twilio Inc.</td>
          <td>SMS delivery — internal escalation notifications to the Client's on-call person.</td>
          <td>Recipient phone number, SMS content.</td>
          <td>USA (outside EEA)</td>
          <td>DPA + SCC</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Hetzner</strong><br />Hetzner Online GmbH</td>
          <td>Hosting of the application infrastructure and database (server, PostgreSQL database).</td>
          <td>All application data stored in the database (accounts, messages, transcripts, records).</td>
          <td><strong>Germany — Nuremberg (EU)</strong></td>
          <td>Data processing agreement (AVV)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">2.</span>Data residency summary</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>AwesomeBot server and database:</strong> Germany — Nuremberg (EU), with Hetzner.</li>
    <li><strong>Telephony (Telnyx):</strong> Germany (EU).</li>
    <li><strong>Voice platform and recordings (ElevenLabs):</strong> with data residency.</li>
    <li><strong>AI models and transcription (OpenAI) and SMS (Twilio):</strong> USA — under SCC and DPAs.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">3.</span>Supporting infrastructure</h2>
  <p>
    To build and deliver the software we also use supporting services (e.g. a code and container-image
    repository and a management network). As a rule these do not process contacting persons' personal
    data during normal operation of the Service; if that changes, they will be added to an updated
    version of this list.
  </p>

  <h2><span class="legal-num">4.</span>Changes to the subprocessor list</h2>
  <p>
    We will inform Clients of any planned addition or change of a subprocessor before entrusting their
    data, allowing a reasoned objection on the terms set out in the DPA. The current version and its
    effective date are published on the Landing. Questions: hello@awesomeworks.ai.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
